##  Service Details

### **User Service** (Port 5000)
**Features:**
- User registration (student/instructor)
- User login with JWT
- Profile management

**Key Routes:**
```
POST   /register          → Register user
POST   /login            → Login user
GET    /:userId          → Get user profile
PUT    /:userId          → Update profile
DELETE /:userId          → Delete user
```

### **Course Service** (Port 5001)
**Features:**
- Create and manage courses
- List available courses
- Course details with modules

**Key Routes:**
```
GET    /all                        → Get all courses
GET    /:courseId                  → Get course details
POST   /create                     → Create course
PUT    /:courseId                  → Update course
DELETE /:courseId                  → Delete course
```

### **Enrollment Service** (Port 5002)
**Features:**
- Student enrollment
- Enrollment management
- Enrollment history

**Key Routes:**
```
POST   /enroll                     → Enroll in course
GET    /my-enrollments             → Get user enrollments
GET    /:enrollmentId              → Get enrollment details
PUT    /:enrollmentId/status       → Update status
DELETE /:enrollmentId/cancel       → Cancel enrollment
```

### **Progress Service** (Port 5003)
**Features:**
- Track lesson completion
- Calculate progress percentage
- Course statistics

**Key Routes:**
```
POST   /track                      → Track progress
GET    /my-progress                → Get user progress
GET    /:progressId                → Get progress details
PUT    /:progressId/score          → Update score
GET    /course/:courseId/stats     → Get course stats
```

### **Certificate Service** (Port 5004)
**Features:**
- Generate certificates
- Verify certificates
- Revoke certificates

**Key Routes:**
```
POST   /generate                   → Generate certificate
GET    /my-certificates            → Get user certificates
GET    /:certificateId             → Get certificate details
GET    /verify/:certificateNumber  → Verify certificate
PUT    /:certificateId/revoke      → Revoke certificate
```

